    short_description:
      'Join The Browser Company as an Engineering Manager for Product Infrastructure, leading a team of software engineers in creating innovative systems and tools for our browser. We seek someone with 8+ years of experience in client-side or C++ infrastructure environments, strong people management skills, and a passion for mentoring and coaching engineers. Enjoy a flexible compensation model, competitive salary range of $180,000-$320,000 USD, and comprehensive benefits package including 401k, flexible vacation policy, and 12 weeks of paid parental leave.',
    job_requirements:
      '• 8+ years of experience leading critical projects or initiatives in client-side or C++ infrastructure environments, with a preference for iOS or MacOS experience, but also open to Android, Windows, or general browser experience.\n• 3+ years of experience in people management, with a strong track record of coaching and mentoring senior engineers to improve their skills and grow their careers.\n• Expertise in tech leading critical projects and initiatives within a team and organization, demonstrating the ability to drive execution and set a pace for successful outcomes.\n• Passion for building tools and systems that enhance the productivity of engineers, with a focus on creating elegant and maintainable solutions.\n• Pragmatic mindset, motivated by complex challenges, and enthusiastic about working in a startup environment with rapid product validation cycles.\n• Ability to work effectively in North American time zones, requiring a minimum of 4+ hours of overlap with team members in the Eastern Time Zone.',
    welcomed_skills:
      '- Strong leadership in C++ infrastructure.\n- Experience in iOS, MacOS, Android, or Windows.\n- Skilled in coaching and mentoring.\n- Proficient in driving execution and setting pace.\n- Passion for building elegant, maintainable tools.\n- Familiarity with North American time zones.\n- Ability to scale a team with company values in mind.',
    skill_tags: ['C++', 'People Management', 'Mentoring', 'Software Engineering', 'Infrastructure'],
    skill_analysis:
      'The job description for the Engineering Manager, Product Infrastructure position at The Browser Company emphasizes a mix of technical expertise, leadership skills, and a passion for mentoring and coaching engineers. The key skills required for this role can be categorized as follows:\n\n1. Client-Side and C++ Infrastructure Experience: The candidate must have a minimum of 8 years of experience in client-side or C++ infrastructure environments, with a preference for iOS or MacOS experience. This expertise is crucial for leading critical projects and initiatives related to browser development.\n\n2. People Management and Mentoring: With at least 3 years of experience in people management, the candidate should possess strong leadership skills in coaching and mentoring senior engineers. The ability to foster team growth, promote knowledge sharing, and drive the career development of team members is essential.\n\n3. Technical Leadership: The candidate must demonstrate expertise in leading technical projects and initiatives within a team and organization. This includes driving execution, setting a pace for successful outcomes, and contributing to the overall technical strategy of the product infrastructure team.\n\n4. Passion for Building Tools and Systems: A key requirement is a passion for building tools and systems that enhance the productivity of engineers. The focus should be on creating elegant and maintainable solutions to support the development of innovative browser features.\n\n5. Pragmatic Mindset and Startup Environment Adaptability: The ideal candidate should have a pragmatic mindset, be motivated by complex challenges, and be enthusiastic about working in a startup environment with rapid product validation cycles.\n\n6. Time Zone Compatibility: The ability to work effectively in North American time zones, particularly with a minimum of 4+ hours of overlap with team members in the Eastern Time Zone, is necessary for seamless collaboration.\n\n7. Additional Welcomed Skills: Skills such as strong leadership in C++ infrastructure, experience in iOS, MacOS, Android, or Windows, proficiency in driving execution and setting pace, familiarity with North American time zones, and the ability to scale a team with company values in mind are also valued.\n',
    comprehensive_skill_tags:
      'Client-Side Development, C++, iOS, MacOS, People Management, Mentoring, Technical Leadership, Project Management, Software Engineering, Infrastructure, Problem-Solving, Startup Environment, Time Management, Communication Skills, Team Collaboration, Leadership, Coaching, Tool Development, System Design, North American Time Zones, Team Scaling',
    description:
      'The Browser Company is seeking an Engineering Manager for the Product Infrastructure team. In this role, you will lead a team of software engineers working on critical projects such as AI-driven personalization features, cross-language platform development, and enhancing Chromium performance. As an Engineering Manager, you will be responsible for managing a team of 6-8 engineers, fostering team growth and health, promoting knowledge sharing, and collaborating with various product teams on technical strategy. You will lead technical projects across different layers, design APIs, ensure efficient product development cycles, and contribute to the broader engineering organization through processes and recruitment. The ideal candidate should have 8+ years of experience in client-side or C++ infrastructure environments, with 3+ years in people management. You should excel in coaching and mentoring senior engineers, driving execution, and building elegant and maintainable systems. A strong passion for solving complex problems and working in a startup environment is essential. The compensation package includes a salary range of $180,000-$320,000 USD, flexible compensation options, comprehensive benefits, 401k plan, flexible vacation policy, parental leave, and various health benefits. Join our diverse and dynamic team at The Browser Company to help shape the future of internet browsing!',
