    short_description:
      'Join Realiste AI as a Financial Management Specialist in Dubai, UAE. Responsibilities include securing financial loans, expediting real estate projects, and reducing overdue accounts. Candidates must have UAE B2B experience, financial literacy, and fluency in Russian and English. Enjoy competitive compensation, career growth opportunities, and potential stock options after 6 months. Apply now to streamline collaboration with real estate developers and financial institutions.',
    job_requirements:
      '• Work experience as a B2B credit broker, B2B development manager, investment attraction manager, or receivables collection specialist (B2B) in the UAE, with a demonstrated track record of success.\n   - Refinement: Proven track record of successfully managing B2B financial transactions in the UAE real estate sector, showcasing expertise in credit brokerage, development management, investment attraction, or receivables collection.\n   \n• Higher education and strong financial literacy.\n   - Refinement: Possession of a relevant higher education degree coupled with a deep understanding of financial concepts and practices within the real estate investment domain.\n   \n• Minimum 2 years of experience in the B2B segment in the UAE.\n   - Refinement: At least 2 years of hands-on experience specifically in the B2B sector in the UAE, demonstrating a comprehensive understanding of the local market dynamics and business practices.\n   \n• Positive reputation at previous workplaces.\n   - Refinement: Demonstrated history of maintaining a positive professional reputation at previous workplaces, highlighting integrity, reliability, and effective collaboration skills.\n   \n• Fluency in both Russian and English languages.\n   - Refinement: Proficiency in both Russian and English languages to facilitate effective communication with a diverse range of stakeholders in the real estate investment sector.\n   \n• Strong negotiation and relationship-building skills.\n   - Refinement: Exceptional ability to negotiate effectively with financial institutions, developers, and other stakeholders, coupled with a talent for building and maintaining strong business relationships to drive successful real estate investment projects.',
    welcomed_skills:
      '- Proficiency in financial modeling and analysis to evaluate real estate investment opportunities effectively.\n- Strong negotiation skills to secure favorable terms for financial loans and real estate deals.\n- Experience in managing accounts receivable and reducing overdue payments to enhance financial stability.\n- Knowledge of the real estate market trends and regulations in the UAE for informed decision-making.\n- Ability to communicate effectively in a multicultural environment and collaborate remotely with global teams.\n- Familiarity with AI technologies and their applications in financial management for strategic decision-making.\n- Proven track record in developing B2B relationships and attracting investments in the real estate sector.',
