    short_description:
      'Seeking a UI Designer and Figma Specialist to lead a complete platform redesign for the Interaction Design Foundation. Utilize advanced Figma functionalities to enhance design systems and visual elements. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver cohesive user experiences. Fully remote position with global impact and growth opportunities.',
    job_requirements:
      '• Minimum 5 years of hands-on experience in UI design, demonstrating expertise in typographic hierarchy, grid systems, color psychology, and micro-interactions.\n• Proficiency in Figma, showcasing advanced skills in utilizing features like auto-layout, variant components, and design tokens to develop scalable and maintainable design systems.\n• Strong problem-solving abilities in visual design, with a focus on refining UI elements to enhance user engagement and visual harmony.\n• Ability to collaborate effectively in multidisciplinary teams, coordinating design efforts with engineers, product managers, and content strategists to deliver cohesive user experiences.\n• Strong organizational skills, capable of breaking down broad responsibilities into manageable tasks and maintaining focus on the overall mission.\n• Results-driven mindset with a passion for achieving goals, a distaste for mediocrity, and a practical idealist approach to balancing perfection with timely execution.',
    welcomed_skills:
      '- Proficiency in Figma, utilizing features like components and design tokens for scalability.\n- Advanced visual design skills, including typographic hierarchy, color psychology, and micro-interactions mastery.\n- Experience in UI design, with a keen eye for pixel-perfect details and visual harmony.\n- Ability to collaborate effectively with engineers, product managers, and content strategists for cohesive user experiences.\n- Strong problem-solving skills in visual design, enhancing user engagement through refined UI elements.\n- Experience in transitioning design systems to Figma, ensuring scalability, efficiency, and reusability.\n- Adept at organizing and maintaining design systems, holding the development team accountable for code maintenance.',
    skill_tags: ['UI Design', 'Figma', 'Design Systems', 'Collaboration', 'Remote Work'],
    skill_analysis:
      '\n\n**Analysis:**\n\n1. **UI Design:**\n   - *Context*: The job description emphasizes the need for a UI Designer with expertise in typographic hierarchy, grid systems, color psychology, and micro-interactions. The candidate should have a keen eye for pixel-perfect details and visual harmony.\n   - *Relevance*: Essential for leading the platform redesign and enhancing user interfaces to improve user experience.\n\n2. **Figma:**\n   - *Context*: Proficiency in Figma is a core requirement, including advanced skills in utilizing features like auto-layout, variant components, and design tokens to develop scalable and maintainable design systems.\n   - *Relevance*: Critical for leading the redesign process and transitioning core flows using Figma.\n\n3. **Design Systems:**\n   - *Context*: The job demands the ability to develop and maintain design systems, ensuring scalability, efficiency, and reusability, specifically in Figma.\n   - *Relevance*: Crucial for creating cohesive user experiences and evolving the IxDF brand identity.\n\n4. **Collaboration:**\n   - *Context*: Collaboration with cross-functional teams, including engineers, product managers, and content strategists, is essential for delivering cohesive user experiences.\n   - *Relevance*: Necessary for coordinating design efforts and ensuring a harmonious user experience.\n\n5. **Remote Work:**\n   - *Context*: The position is fully remote, requiring strong organizational skills to manage tasks effectively and maintain focus on the overall mission.\n   - *Relevance*: Important for success in a remote work environment and achieving goals independently.\n\n6. **Problem-Solving:**\n   - *Context*: Strong problem-solving abilities in visual design are needed to refine UI elements, enhance user engagement, and achieve visual harmony.\n   - *Relevance*: Critical for improving user engagement and ensuring a high-quality user interface.\n\n7. **Results-Driven Mindset:**\n   - *Context*: The job description values a results-driven mindset with a passion for achieving goals and a practical idealist approach to balancing perfection with timely execution.\n   - *Relevance*: Important for meeting project goals, maintaining high standards, and achieving excellence.\n\n**Skill Tags:** UI Design, Figma, Design Systems, Collaboration, Remote Work, Problem-Solving, Results-Driven Mindset',
    comprehensive_skill_tags:
      'UI Design, Figma, Design Systems, Collaboration, Remote Work, Problem-Solving, Results-Driven Mindset',
    description:
      'Are you a talented UI Designer with a passion for creating inspiring and enduring user interfaces? The Interaction Design Foundation (IxDF) is seeking a UI Designer and Figma Specialist to join our team in Denmark. As the biggest online design school globally, we are dedicated to providing premier design education to thousands of individuals and organizations worldwide. In this fully remote, full-time position, you will play a crucial role in redesigning our platform using Figma, transitioning core flows, and focusing on visual design details to enhance user experience. Your responsibilities will also include maintaining and evolving our design system, collaborating with various teams, and contributing to the IxDF brand identity. To excel in this role, you must have extensive experience in UI design, advanced visual design skills, and proficiency in Figma. You should be a problem-solver with a keen eye for detail, possess strong collaboration skills, and be results-driven with a passion for achieving excellence. If you are based within UTC+1 to UTC+5 time zones and are ready to take on the challenge of shaping the future of online design education, we encourage you to apply. Join us at IxDF and be part of a dynamic team where your contributions will make a significant impact on the global design community. Apply now and embark on a rewarding journey of growth and innovation with us!',
